def: A small South American bird (Anumbius anumbii) allied to theovenbirds of the genus Furnarius). It builds a very large and complexnest of twigs and thorns in a bush or tree.

Dependent upon, or appertaining to, another thing, called theprincipal. Incident proposition (Logic), a proposition subordinate toanother, and introduced by who, which, whose, whom, etc.; as, Julius,whose surname was CÃ¦sar, overcame Pompey. I. Watts.
Adamant. [Obs.]Written in the table of athamaunt. Chaucer.
A fox; -- so called in fables or familiar tales, and in poetry.[Written also reynard.]
The act of stultifying, or the state of being stultified.
One of the granular masses which constitute a racemose orcompound gland, as the pancreas; also, one of the saccular recessesin the lobules of a racemose gland. Quain.
An animal of the barnacle tribe, of the genus Lepas, having afleshy stem or peduncle; a goose barnacle. See Cirripedia.
A falling off. [R.] Sir T. Browne.
